 mutate { add_tag => ["processed_at_middleman"] } 
} 
 
output { 
 elasticsearch { 
   hosts => ["https://our-es-cluster:9200"] 
   index => "products_search" 
 } 
} 

 

Summary Recommendation for Option 4 

We recommend this approach if we need to clean or transform data heavily before it reaches Elasticsearch, but we don't want to manage the full complexity of Kafka (Option 2). It provides a great balance of flexibility and centralized management, especially if we have multiple different apps that all need to send data to the same search engine. 

 

 

 

 

 
